summary: It’s easy to forget Taylor Swift’s songwriting pedigree since it seems like she’s always been the-larger-than-life pop star...
text: It’s easy to forget Taylor Swift’s songwriting pedigree since it seems like she’s always been the-larger-than-life pop star she’s known as today, but Swift is steeped in the Nashville songwriter tradition. At the age of 16 she released her self-titled debut with songwriting credits on every track and continued to hone her skills over the next decade. While most pop songs are known for their universality, Swift very much follows in the confessional singer-songwriter tradition of artists like James Taylor and Carole King, making each song distinctly her own. Along with writing albums like her breakthrough Speak Now and her crossover album Red, she’s also penned hits for other artists, including Little Big Town’s ‘Better Man’, ‘You’ll Always Find Your Way Back Home’ by Miley Cyrus and ‘This Is What You Came For’ by Calvin Harris.
source: Taylor Swift is listed as #20 on Best Female Songwriters list made by uDiscover Music (March 21st 2019)

answer:
Yeah, Taylor liked Sophie Turner’s Instagram video…

…took me some time to find where you got that following information - I’m sure certain people have extra options on Instagram, and Taylor would be one of those people able to ask for customized extra options. I remember they asked Blake Lively once about her Simple Favor promo and all the Instagram shenanigans and she said something like, “you can ask for and get some special features when you’re celebrity”… so who knows, I would be more surprised to find they use the same Instagram that all the rest of us do…
